SIMPLE: photolithograph
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Photolithograph
<hw>Pho`to*lith"o*graph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Photo-</ets> + <ets>lithograph</ets>.]</ety> <def>A
lithographic picture or copy from a stone prepared by the aid of
photography.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Photolithograph</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Photolithograph
<hw>Pho`to*lith"o*graph</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To produce (a
picture, a copy) by the process of photolithography.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Photolithographer</ent>⟦br⟧
